Conus tabidus is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.Like all species within the genus Conus, these snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should be handled carefully or not at all.
Unilke other Conus species in the waters off the continent which its synonymy is Africonus, the synonymy for this one is Monteiroconus.